# noSwag Password Manager - Environment Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual values

# ===========================================
# OPTION 1: Gmail App Password (RECOMMENDED)
# ===========================================
EMAIL_ADDRESS=your-email@gmail.com
EMAIL_PASSWORD=your-16-character-app-password

# Gmail App Password Setup Instructions:
# 1. Enable 2-Factor Authentication on your Gmail account
# 2. Go to https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords
# 3. Select "Mail" as the app type
# 4. Generate the 16-character app password
# 5. Use that password above (NOT your regular Gmail password)
# 6. Keep your .env file secure and add it to .gitignore

# Optional SMTP Configuration (defaults work for Gmail)
SMTP_SERVER=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=587

# ===========================================
# OPTION 2: Google Service Account (ADVANCED)
# ===========================================
# If you prefer using Gmail API with service account:
# GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON=path/to/service-account-key.json
# GOOGLE_PROJECT_ID=your-google-cloud-project-id
# SENDER_EMAIL=your-email@gmail.com

# Service Account Setup Instructions:
# 1. Create a Google Cloud Project
# 2. Enable Gmail API
# 3. Create a service account with Gmail send permissions
# 4. Download the JSON key file
# 5. Grant domain-wide delegation if sending from your domain